The paper deals with online routing in planar geometric graphs, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the weight and degree of the graph, which are properties related to data structures (cs.DS). The use of a minimum spanning tree and the construction of a planar geometric graph suggest that the paper may also be relevant to network optimization (cs.NE) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes a routing strategy, which is a topic related to computer networks (cs.SI).
